author: cmpilato
msg: Add new 'propsetf' subcommand to 'svnmucc'.  This allows folks to more
easily set binary and multi-line property values.
* tools/client-side/svnmucc/svnmucc.c
(ACTION_PROPSETF): New enum value.
(struct operation): Lose 'props' member in favor of 'prop_mods' and
'prop_dels' members.
(struct driver_state, set_props): Removed as unused.
(change_props, read_propvalue_file): New helper functions.
(drive): Now use change_props(), and track changes in the data types
used for property handling.
(get_operation): Track changes in the data types used for property handling.
(build): Change 'prop_value' parameter type to 'const svn_string_t *',
and now employ the new bifurcated prop-change storage structures
in 'struct operation'.
(struct action): Make 'prop_value' member into a 'const svn_string_t *'.
(execute): Handle ACTION_PROPSETF and default switch cases (with abort).
(main): Handle new 'propsetf' subcommand.
